            <h1> Expected Completion: 2031 </h1>

            <h2> Get across town 60% faster </h2>
            <p> New, reliable rapid transit is coming to Toronto with the Lawrence Crosstown Light Rail Transit (LRT) project. With 13 stations and stops running east-west across midtown Toronto, we're building the new Crosstown LRT to get you get you
                where you need to be better, faster and easier. </p>
            <p> It will give families like yours the freedom to live, work and play, in a city always growing into something greater. </p>
            <p> The 52 Lawrence West route is the busiest TTC bus route in the City, carrying nearly 44,000 customers on a typical weekday. The 52 Lawrence has an average frequency of approximately a bus every 3 minutes but severe traffic congestion makes
                headways unpredicatable and your commute longer than it should be.</p>
            <p> Existing plans and modifications to Lawrence are simply not enough to handle the thousands of commuters and length traffic times along Lawrence West. </p>

