            <h2> Connections </h2>
            <p> A true example of a new regional rapid transit network, the Crosstown will link to TTC 24 bus routes, two TTC subway stations (Lawrence Heights and Lawrence), and two GO stations (Weston and Joyce), all featuring 15-minute or better service
                and new stations, to connect you to your city.
            </p>

            <h2> Speed </h2>
            <p> Move across 13 kilometres faster than a streetcar, a bus, or a rideshare. In fact, your Crosstown LRT vehicle will be up to 60% faster than your current travel time. How's that for fast?
            </p>

            <h2> Relief </h2>
            <p> Between Weston Station and Leaside Station, TTC bus routes will be replaced and upgraded with light rail vehicles traveling underground and in dedicated lanes, outside of traffic. With fewer buses and more drivers switching to transit,
                everyone will enjoy a different kind of transit journey. That's a benefit for everyone.
            </p>

            <h2> Project Overview </h2>
            <p> The Lawrence Crosstown is the cornerstone of the $6 billion investment. The Midtown line will run underground for more than 13 kilometres, from Weston Road to Bayview Avenue and down to Eglinton Avenue.</p>
            <p> The project, which is under construction now, is creating thousands of design and construction jobs, and will provide lasting economic benefits to Toronto and its surrounding region.</p>
            <p> For employers, public transit is how their workforce commutes. For thousands of students, it's how they get to class. For seniors, it's how they get to their medical appointments and maintain independence in their senior years. Once complete,
                the Crosstown service will cut transit time significantly along this important mid-town corridor.
            </p>

            <h2> Future Extensions </h2>
            <p> Later phases include extensions to Pearson International Airport and through Scarborough all the way to Rouge Park Station. </p>
            <p>The Crosstown will open as Line 9 Lawrence, in 2031. Monitor construction progress and milestones by visiting the Crosstown website at www.thecrosstown.ca.</p>

